com.yworks.yfiles.view.input

Interface IStripeInputVisualizationHelper

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultStripeInputVisualizationHelper

    public interface IStripeInputVisualizationHelper
    This interface allows to change the visualization for different input gestures.

    A stripe should provide an implementation of this interface in its lookup which is queried by the various table related input modes.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      IVisualCreator getVisualCreator(IInputModeContext context, INode tableNode, StripeVisualizationType type)

    • Method Detail

      • getVisualCreator

        IVisualCreator getVisualCreator(IInputModeContext context,
                                INode tableNode,
                                StripeVisualizationType type)
        Return an IVisualCreator that is used to visualize the input operation specified by type.
        Parameters:
        context - The input mode context which provides further information.
        tableNode - The node where the stripe's owner is currently bound to.
        type - The actual visualization type
        Returns:
        A IVisualCreator instance that renders a representation for the current operation.
